<Layout title="Closing a Capital One Account After a Death" description="Step-by-step guide to closing or managing a Capital One account after someone has died. Capital One processes most estate claims by mail.">

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/accounts/bank-accounts/">Bank Accounts</a> › Capital One</div>
  <h1>Closing a Capital One Account After a Death</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Capital One is primarily an online bank. Most of this process happens by phone and mail, expect slower turnaround than banks with branch networks.</p>
</div>

<section class="card">
  <h2>How to start</h2>
  <p>Call <strong>Capital One Estate Administration: 1-888-810-4013</strong>. They will provide their mailing address and fax number for submitting documentation.</p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>What to submit</h2>
  <p>Capital One processes estate claims primarily by mail or fax:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certified death certificate</li>
    <li>A copy of your government-issued photo ID</li>
    <li>Letters testamentary or letters of administration</li>
    <li>Account numbers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>When you call, ask for the current mailing address and fax number. These can change; always confirm when you call rather than using an address from an old document.</p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>What to expect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Capital One 360 savings and checking accounts:</strong> Frozen upon notification, released to executor with proper documentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Joint accounts:</strong> Transfer to surviving owner.</li>
    <li><strong>POD accounts:</strong> Beneficiary claims with death certificate and ID.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Capital One credit card balances are the estate's responsibility, not yours personally, unless you were a joint account holder.</p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Capital One Auto Finance</h2>
  <p>If continuing payments on a vehicle you're keeping: <strong>1-800-946-0332</strong>. Contact them to update the account to your name.</p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Timeline</h2>
  <p>4 to 10 weeks, due to the mail-based process. Build in extra time. Mail the documents, note the date you sent them, and follow up in three weeks if you haven't heard back.</p>
</section>

<div class="can-wait">
  <strong>Capital One's process is slow. That's not your fault.</strong> Mail the documents, note the date, follow up in three weeks.
</div>

</Layout>
